The paper proposes a downsampled variant of ImageNet for training deep neural networks, which is a common task in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses algorithm design, architecture search, and hyperparameter tuning, which are topics related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of natural language processing techniques for analyzing the results, which falls under computational linguistics (cs.CL).
